None in this slice.

## Dead Ends
Linking instead of excluding (parent the generateContent op under the ADK
call_llm call, like openai.ts does with openai-agents): needs ambient
correlation at generateContent time; without weave owning the global OTel
ContextManager there is none that survives ParallelAgent. Both calls also
carry usage, which would double-count tokens in trace rollups.

## Hints for Future Agents
- The marker is ADK's BaseLlm.trackingHeaders; if ADK renames the header or
  drops the 'google-adk/' label the exclusion silently stops and ADK runs
  start showing duplicate usage (google.adk.call_llm + orphan root
  google.genai.models.generateContent traces). The integration test in PR
  3/4 pins the current behavior.
- User-supplied headers merge AFTER trackingHeaders in getHttpOptions, so a
  user could in theory overwrite x-goog-api-client and re-enable wrapping
  inside ADK; not worth defending against.

